  10 def asdict(
  11     inst,
  12     recurse=True,
  13     filter=None,
  14     dict_factory=dict,
  15     retain_collection_types=False,
  16 ):
  17     """
  18     Return the ``attrs`` attribute values of *inst* as a dict.
  19 
  20     Optionally recurse into other ``attrs``-decorated classes.
  21 
  22     :param inst: Instance of an ``attrs``-decorated class.
  23     :param bool recurse: Recurse into classes that are also
  24         ``attrs``-decorated.
  25     :param callable filter: A callable whose return code determines whether an
  26         attribute or element is included (``True``) or dropped (``False``).  Is
  27         called with the `attr.Attribute` as the first argument and the
  28         value as the second argument.
  29     :param callable dict_factory: A callable to produce dictionaries from.  For
  30         example, to produce ordered dictionaries instead of normal Python
  31         dictionaries, pass in ``collections.OrderedDict``.
  32     :param bool retain_collection_types: Do not convert to ``list`` when
  33         encountering an attribute whose type is ``tuple`` or ``set``.  Only
  34         meaningful if ``recurse`` is ``True``.
  35 
  36     :rtype: return type of *dict_factory*
  37 
  38     :raise attr.exceptions.NotAnAttrsClassError: If *cls* is not an ``attrs``
  39         class.
  40 
  41     ..  versionadded:: 16.0.0 *dict_factory*
  42     ..  versionadded:: 16.1.0 *retain_collection_types*
  43     """
  44     attrs = fields(inst.__class__)
  45     rv = dict_factory()
  46     for a in attrs:
  47         v = getattr(inst, a.name)
  48         if filter is not None and not filter(a, v):
  49             continue
  50         if recurse is True:
  51             if has(v.__class__):
  52                 rv[a.name] = asdict(
  53                     v, True, filter, dict_factory, retain_collection_types
  54                 )
  55             elif isinstance(v, (tuple, list, set)):
  56                 cf = v.__class__ if retain_collection_types is True else list
  57                 rv[a.name] = cf(
  58                     [
  59                         _asdict_anything(
  60                             i, filter, dict_factory, retain_collection_types
  61                         )
  62                         for i in v
  63                     ]
  64                 )
  65             elif isinstance(v, dict):
  66                 df = dict_factory
  67                 rv[a.name] = df(
  68                     (
  69                         _asdict_anything(
  70                             kk, filter, df, retain_collection_types
  71                         ),
  72                         _asdict_anything(
  73                             vv, filter, df, retain_collection_types
  74                         ),
  75                     )
  76                     for kk, vv in iteritems(v)
  77                 )
  78             else:
  79                 rv[a.name] = v
  80         else:
  81             rv[a.name] = v
  82     return rv
  83 
  84 
  85 def _asdict_anything(val, filter, dict_factory, retain_collection_types):
  86     """
  87     ``asdict`` only works on attrs instances, this works on anything.
  88     """
  89     if getattr(val.__class__, "__attrs_attrs__", None) is not None:
  90         # Attrs class.
  91         rv = asdict(val, True, filter, dict_factory, retain_collection_types)
  92     elif isinstance(val, (tuple, list, set)):
  93         cf = val.__class__ if retain_collection_types is True else list
  94         rv = cf(
  95             [
  96                 _asdict_anything(
  97                     i, filter, dict_factory, retain_collection_types
  98                 )
  99                 for i in val
 100             ]
 101         )
 102     elif isinstance(val, dict):
 103         df = dict_factory
 104         rv = df(
 105             (
 106                 _asdict_anything(kk, filter, df, retain_collection_types),
 107                 _asdict_anything(vv, filter, df, retain_collection_types),
 108             )
 109             for kk, vv in iteritems(val)
 110         )
 111     else:
 112         rv = val
 113     return rv

 116 def astuple(
 117     inst,
 118     recurse=True,
 119     filter=None,
 120     tuple_factory=tuple,
 121     retain_collection_types=False,
 122 ):
 123     """
 124     Return the ``attrs`` attribute values of *inst* as a tuple.
 125 
 126     Optionally recurse into other ``attrs``-decorated classes.
 127 
 128     :param inst: Instance of an ``attrs``-decorated class.
 129     :param bool recurse: Recurse into classes that are also
 130         ``attrs``-decorated.
 131     :param callable filter: A callable whose return code determines whether an
 132         attribute or element is included (``True``) or dropped (``False``).  Is
 133         called with the `attr.Attribute` as the first argument and the
 134         value as the second argument.
 135     :param callable tuple_factory: A callable to produce tuples from.  For
 136         example, to produce lists instead of tuples.
 137     :param bool retain_collection_types: Do not convert to ``list``
 138         or ``dict`` when encountering an attribute which type is
 139         ``tuple``, ``dict`` or ``set``.  Only meaningful if ``recurse`` is
 140         ``True``.
 141 
 142     :rtype: return type of *tuple_factory*
 143 
 144     :raise attr.exceptions.NotAnAttrsClassError: If *cls* is not an ``attrs``
 145         class.
 146 
 147     ..  versionadded:: 16.2.0
 148     """
 149     attrs = fields(inst.__class__)
 150     rv = []
 151     retain = retain_collection_types  # Very long. :/
 152     for a in attrs:
 153         v = getattr(inst, a.name)
 154         if filter is not None and not filter(a, v):
 155             continue
 156         if recurse is True:
 157             if has(v.__class__):
 158                 rv.append(
 159                     astuple(
 160                         v,
 161                         recurse=True,
 162                         filter=filter,
 163                         tuple_factory=tuple_factory,
 164                         retain_collection_types=retain,
 165                     )
 166                 )
 167             elif isinstance(v, (tuple, list, set)):
 168                 cf = v.__class__ if retain is True else list
 169                 rv.append(
 170                     cf(
 171                         [
 172                             astuple(
 173                                 j,
 174                                 recurse=True,
 175                                 filter=filter,
 176                                 tuple_factory=tuple_factory,
 177                                 retain_collection_types=retain,
 178                             )
 179                             if has(j.__class__)
 180                             else j
 181                             for j in v
 182                         ]
 183                     )
 184                 )
 185             elif isinstance(v, dict):
 186                 df = v.__class__ if retain is True else dict
 187                 rv.append(
 188                     df(
 189                         (
 190                             astuple(
 191                                 kk,
 192                                 tuple_factory=tuple_factory,
 193                                 retain_collection_types=retain,
 194                             )
 195                             if has(kk.__class__)
 196                             else kk,
 197                             astuple(
 198                                 vv,
 199                                 tuple_factory=tuple_factory,
 200                                 retain_collection_types=retain,
 201                             )
 202                             if has(vv.__class__)
 203                             else vv,
 204                         )
 205                         for kk, vv in iteritems(v)
 206                     )
 207                 )
 208             else:
 209                 rv.append(v)
 210         else:
 211             rv.append(v)
 212     return rv if tuple_factory is list else tuple_factory(rv)

 215 def has(cls):
 216     """
 217     Check whether *cls* is a class with ``attrs`` attributes.
 218 
 219     :param type cls: Class to introspect.
 220     :raise TypeError: If *cls* is not a class.
 221 
 222     :rtype: bool
 223     """
 224     return getattr(cls, "__attrs_attrs__", None) is not None
 225

 227 def assoc(inst, **changes):
 228     """
 229     Copy *inst* and apply *changes*.
 230 
 231     :param inst: Instance of a class with ``attrs`` attributes.
 232     :param changes: Keyword changes in the new copy.
 233 
 234     :return: A copy of inst with *changes* incorporated.
 235 
 236     :raise attr.exceptions.AttrsAttributeNotFoundError: If *attr_name* couldn't
 237         be found on *cls*.
 238     :raise attr.exceptions.NotAnAttrsClassError: If *cls* is not an ``attrs``
 239         class.
 240 
 241     ..  deprecated:: 17.1.0
 242         Use `evolve` instead.
 243     """
 244     import warnings
 245 
 246     warnings.warn(
 247         "assoc is deprecated and will be removed after 2018/01.",
 248         DeprecationWarning,
 249         stacklevel=2,
 250     )
 251     new = copy.copy(inst)
 252     attrs = fields(inst.__class__)
 253     for k, v in iteritems(changes):
 254         a = getattr(attrs, k, NOTHING)
 255         if a is NOTHING:
 256             raise AttrsAttributeNotFoundError(
 257                 "{k} is not an attrs attribute on {cl}.".format(
 258                     k=k, cl=new.__class__
 259                 )
 260             )
 261         _obj_setattr(new, k, v)
 262     return new
 263

 265 def evolve(inst, **changes):
 266     """
 267     Create a new instance, based on *inst* with *changes* applied.
 268 
 269     :param inst: Instance of a class with ``attrs`` attributes.
 270     :param changes: Keyword changes in the new copy.
 271 
 272     :return: A copy of inst with *changes* incorporated.
 273 
 274     :raise TypeError: If *attr_name* couldn't be found in the class
 275         ``__init__``.
 276     :raise attr.exceptions.NotAnAttrsClassError: If *cls* is not an ``attrs``
 277         class.
 278 
 279     ..  versionadded:: 17.1.0
 280     """
 281     cls = inst.__class__
 282     attrs = fields(cls)
 283     for a in attrs:
 284         if not a.init:
 285             continue
 286         attr_name = a.name  # To deal with private attributes.
 287         init_name = attr_name if attr_name[0] != "_" else attr_name[1:]
 288         if init_name not in changes:
 289             changes[init_name] = getattr(inst, attr_name)
 290     return cls(**changes)
